# Rule: ń”üconsole_log
# Token: ń”üconsole_log_production
# Priority: P0 (HIGHEST)
# Source: NeuronFS Governance Defaults

ń”üconsole_log Õ┐ģvorq

FORBIDDEN: console.log, print(), System.out.println in production code
REASON: Pollutes logs, leaks debugging info in production, performance impact

REPLACEMENT:
    Python:   import logging; logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
    JavaScript: const logger = require('./logger'); or structured logging lib
    Java:      import org.slf4j.Logger; LoggerFactory.getLogger()

EXAMPLE VIOLATION:
    console.log("User logged in:", user);  # BAD ŌØī
    print(user_id)  # BAD ŌØī

CORRECT:
    logger.info("User action completed", extra={"user_id": user_id})  # GOOD Ō£ģ

EXCEPTION:
    - Test files (*.test.js, *_test.py, *Test.java)
    - Development-only code under DEBUG flags
    - CLI tools (print output is expected)
    - scripts/ directory

